caption: Service was great, but the food was disappointing. I found the spot really really expensive. Not a huge fan of the covid recovery fee on the bill. Didn’t see any notice about this.

My girlfriend and I went to Bar Bruno for the first time last night. I feel like I've been fortunate to generally have good meals when I go to restaurants, but the food at Bar Bruno was a cut above.  We ordered hibiscus margaritas, which were good, and some tasty chicken wings as an appetizer. She got tacos for her main, and I ordered what I consider the star of the show, a pulled pork torta.  It came with a chili dip, which was unbelievably smoky and flavorful and stuck to the sandwich like icing on a cake. The bread was soft and fresh and the pulled pork was perfectly cooked. It was the best torta I've ever eaten.  Beyond the food, the service was great. Our waiter, Orlin, was attentive and nice to talk to. I highly recommend Bar Bruno and I know I'll be back.

DELICIOUS!!! We Just moved to the neighborhood and  we have been trying all the restaurants in the area and I literally just finished eating the best grilled chicken burrito I have ever eaten. I am born and raised here and have eaten hundreds of burritos.  It was served with a huge mixed green salad that was done right. If you already eat here you know what I’m talking about and if you are undecided please take my word, you won’t be disappointed. A note on customer service; 5 stars! There was an error on my order and when I called they were incredibly professional and genuinely nice about everything and fixed it in like literally 10 minutes! This has happened to me at other restaurants and I have been met with poor attitude and sometimes afraid to call. I’m sorry I didn’t get his name and the delivery guy so the compliments get noticed.

My brother and I came here while waiting for a late reservation at a place down the street. I ordered the Rosa Rita (reposado, raspberries, pink peppercorn, Cointreau, agave, jasmine flowers). I usually hate tequila drinks (or rather, tequila drinks hate me), but this was delicious.  Then we ordered the guacamole. I was tentative because it features pumpkin seeds, but this is hands down the best guacamole I’ve ever had. My brother agreed! We then split a steak quesadilla and some grilled zucchini. Both were amazing.  The bartender, Sara, was great. The owners were on-site, greeting people and working the room. Fantastic service. I could totally ditch the other reservation and go back to my hotel happy as a clam.

Ordered frozen margaritas, carnitas tacos, steak tacos with rice and beans and tortilla soup. The carnitas were cooked perfectly but we're missing a bit of salt to enhance the flavor of the pork. My husband had the steak tacos - he wasn't thrilled about them. I'm guessing they cut back on the salt due to their clientele. 🤷🏽‍♀️  The service was on point. Chill, casual ambiance.. Might come back for the soup.

For people living in the Carroll Gardens neighborhood, I would recommend any other place than Bar Bruno.   As a local resident that's given this restaurant a ton of business since the first day they opened, it's disheartening that they take our business for granted and would rather use gimmicks to eek out a few more dollars from us and the other loyal neighbors. If this is how they want to grow their business then they can do it without our patronage.

The service can be iffy, but if you get there on a good night, you'll love the freshly made guacamole, fish tacos, and margaritas. I'm also a fan of the kale salad topped with shrimp. It's so hearty it won't feel like a salad.
